</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE2369BFFFEAE5607BEFB8B0083810B" blockId="2.[151,1436,1040,1296]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">
<number id="3D9524BCFFFEAE5607BEFB8B05B58021" box="[151,163,1040,1061]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="5.0">5</number>
Truncate cylindrical setae forming medial and submedial longitudinal rows on thorax and abdomen................... 
<number id="3D9524BCFFFEAE5602ADFB8B00998021" box="[1412,1423,1040,1061]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="5.0">5</number>
b - Truncate setae not forming various rows................................................................... 
<number id="3D9524BCFFFEAE5602B9FBB6008A8046" box="[1424,1436,1069,1090]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="6.0">6</number>
<number id="3D9524BCFFFEAE5607BEFBD105B4805B" box="[151,162,1098,1119]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="5.0">5</number>
b Large stout setae with parallel sides each less than 
<number id="3D9524BCFFFEAE5605F3FBD107EE805B" box="[730,760,1098,1119]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as long as wide, present in medial and submedial longitudinal rows; simple pores entirely absent or rare on dorsum of abdomen; 
<number id="3D9524BCFFFEAE560443FBF306948079" box="[874,898,1128,1149]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="10.0">10</number>
or more wide-rimmed quinquelocular pores per cluster uncommon, and not forming distinctive transverse bands; host-plant 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D18FFFEAE56045DFB1E0110809E" box="[884,1030,1157,1178]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Cylindropuntia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B929EA89FFFEAE56045DFB1E0110809E" box="[884,1030,1157,1178]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Cylindropuntia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp.................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D18FFFEAE56023AFB1E008A809E" box="[1299,1436,1157,1178]" class="Insecta" family="Dactylopiidae" genus="Dactylopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tomentosus">
<emphasis id="B929EA89FFFEAE56023AFB1E008A809E" box="[1299,1436,1157,1178]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">D. tomentosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- Large truncate setae with parallel sides each 
<number id="3D9524BCFFFEAE5605A6FB3907D380B3" box="[655,709,1186,1207]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5â€“2</number>
times as long as wide, present in medial longitudinal rows, submedial rows less distinctive and made up of smaller setae; dorsum with abundant simple pores; clusters of wide-rimmed quinquelocular pores with more than 
<number id="3D9524BCFFFEAE56069BFB4604DC80F6" box="[434,458,1245,1266]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="10.0">10</number>
pores per cluster common, forming distinctive transverse bands; host-plant 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D18FFFEAE56038AFB46003E80F6" box="[1187,1320,1245,1266]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Corynopuntia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B929EA89FFFEAE56038AFB46003E80F6" box="[1187,1320,1245,1266]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Corynopuntia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp........................................................................................ 
